<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy | CourtScope"><section class="hero"><div class="prose-width"><p class="eyebrow">Public policy</p><h1>Privacy Policy</h1><p class="lede">CourtScope minimizes personal information and separates public data from restricted evidence.</p></div></section><section class="section"><div class="prose-width"><div class="card"><p>Public case pages never display defendant names. Correction reporter emails are private and scheduled for deletion 90 days after closure. Raw IP addresses are not retained; salted abuse-prevention hashes may be used. Restricted source artifacts remain private unless a lawful, ethical public release is approved.</p><h2>City-data submissions</h2><p>Files uploaded through the Add a City page are stored in private evidence storage, not in the public website or Git repository. Submission contact details are visible only to authorized administrators. Uploaded packages may be retained while they are reviewed, processed, rejected, investigated, or placed in the controlled cleanup queue.</p><p>Do not upload defendant names, addresses, Social Security numbers, phone numbers, email addresses, or other direct identifiers through the automated repository-ready form. Contact <a href="mailto:data@courtscope.org">data@courtscope.org</a> before transferring raw records.</p><h2>What controls</h2><p>Official source terms, applicable law, dataset-specific notices, and the current published CourtScope methodology control where they are more specific. Contact <a href="mailto:info@courtscope.org">info@courtscope.org</a> for questions.</p><p><strong>Last updated:</strong> July 13, 2026</p></div></div></section></BaseLayout>